{[%mdl 33] INFORCHESS - La Partida del Dнa (Nъmero 923 - 29/11/2003)} {Game 10
A.Anderssen-W.Steinitz Vienna 1873 Ruy Lopez Space matters in chess,
especially when its possession, as in Steinitz’s masterly rout against
Anderssen, at Vienna 1873, severely restricts the mobility and co-ordination
of an opponent’s forces. Anderssen’s queen, in particular, finds itself
completely cut off in an effective prison in White’s own queenside corner.
Steinitz then gains square after square across the entire board, until
Black’s superior, localized army pours in through wide gaps in White’s
over-stretched kingside. Anderssen perhaps all too riskily tempted fate by
repeating the first 9 moves of Zukertort’s loss in the 5th matchgame against
Steinitz, at London 1872 (see Game 9). Steinitz certainly got his own
improvement in first, causing Anderssen, who completely failed to develop a
convincing plan against it, to crash quite catastrophically.} 1. e4 e5 2. Nf3
Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Ba4 Nf6 5. d3 d6 ({Otra posibilidad es} 5... b5 6. Bb3 Bc5 (
6... d6 7. c3 Be7 8. Nbd2 O-O 9. Nf1 {Bronstein-Hebden, partida que fue premio
de belleza, en Londres 1989.} (9. Bc2 d5)) 7. c3 d5 {Weiss-Pollock, partida
que fue premio de belleza en New York 1889.}) 6. Bxc6+ (6. c3 {
Steinitz-Blackburne, Londres 1869.}) 6... bxc6 7. h3 g6 8. Nc3 Bg7 9. Be3 Rb8
10. b3 c5 11. Qd2 h6 12. g4 {[#]} (12. O-O) 12... Ng8 $3 {[%cal Gg8e7,Ge7c6,
Gc6d4] En camino hacia la casilla "d4".} 13. O-O-O Ne7 14. Ne2 Nc6 15. Qc3 Nd4
16. Nfg1 O-O $15 17. Ng3 Be6 18. N1e2 Qd7 19. Bxd4 {Es difнcil sugerir (y
encontrar) un plan constructivo para las blancas.} cxd4 20. Qb2 a5 21. Kd2 d5
$17 22. f3 Qe7 23. Rdf1 Qb4+ 24. Kd1 a4 25. Rh2 c5 26. Nc1 c4 27. a3 Qe7 28. b4
c3 29. Qa1 {Esta situaciуn hace recordar la triste suerte de la dama negra en
la partida Nimzowitsch-Hakanson, Kristianstad 1922.} Qg5 30. Rff2 f5 31. exf5
gxf5 32. h4 Qg6 33. Nxf5 Bxf5 34. gxf5 Rxf5 35. Ne2 Rbf8 36. Qa2 Qf7 37. Rh3
Kh7 38. Ng1 Bf6 39. Ke2 Rg8 40. Kf1 Be7 41. Ne2 Rh5 42. f4 Bxh4 43. Rff3 e4 44.
dxe4 Qg6 45. Ng3 Bxg3 {Este lento estrangulamiento llevado a cabo por Steinitz,
ofrece un contraste manifiesto con las partidas de Paul Morphy.} 0-1

